Logical Chaos v0.1

Tested using Ruby 1.9.3-p484 --> require 'mkmf' problems with newer versions when using selenium web driver
1. Install firefox
2. Install ruby 1.9.3 and 2.0
	2.1 Using rvm (recommended): 
		\curl -sSL https://get.rvm.io | bash
		/bin/bash --login
		rvm install 1.9.3
		rvm use 1.9.3 --default
		Note: if you are using Backtrack or Kali you will have to map the full path /usr/local/rvm/bin/rvm
	2.2 Using apt (not recommended):
 		sudo apt-get install ruby1.9.3-dev
3. Install selenium-webriver 2.4.1 gem:
	gem install selenium-webdriver -v 2.4.1 
4. Install tesseract for captcha support http://code.google.com/p/tesseract-ocr/wiki/Compiling (THIS PART IS STILL IN DEVELOPMENT)

> ruby logical_chaos.rb
> ruby logical_chaos.rb -b
> ruby logical_chaos.rb -e